-- Qantas bid group says considering alternatives
-- 
-- Fri Mar 23, 2007 12:29am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/23/us-qantas-shareholder-apa-idUSSYU00203420070323

 

 SYDNEY  (Reuters) - A Macquarie Bank Ltd. MBL.AX led consortium bidding for Qantas Airways Ltd. ( QAN.AX ) said on Friday it was considering alternatives after a key shareholder said it would not accept the offer. 

 "Airline Partners Australia is considering a range of alternatives in light of the announcement," the consortium said in a statement. Balanced Equity Management said earlier it did not plan to accept the A$5.45-per-share offer. The bid group also includes private equity firm Texas Pacific Group TPG.UL, Allco Equity Partners AEQ.AX, Allco Finance Group AFG.AX and Canadian investment firm Onex Corp ( OCX.TO ).